Section 1:
Act 976 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S4/8/25 S4/14/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1865
4
5 By: Representatives Vaught, Gazaway, Barnett, M. Brown, Hudson, L. Johnson, Maddox, Pearce, R.
6 Scott Richardson, Rose, Clowney
7 By: Senators Gilmore, C. Tucker
8
For An Act To Be Entitled
9
10 AN ACT TO CREATE AN ENHANCED PENALTY FOR CERTAIN
11 OFFENSES AGAINST A CHILD; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO CREATE AN ENHANCED PENALTY FOR
16 CERTAIN OFFENSES AGAINST A CHILD.
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
19
20 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 5, Chapter 4, Subchapter 7, is amended
21 to add an additional section to read as follows:
22 5-4-708. Enhanced penalty for offenses committed against child.
23 (a) A person who is eighteen (18) years of age or older and commits a
24 felony offense described in subsection (b) of this section is subject to an
25 enhanced penalty under this section if:
26 (1) The offense is committed against a child; and
27 (2) The person is in a position of trust or authority over the
28 child.
29 (b) The enhanced penalty in this section applies to a felony offense
30 listed below or contained in the following chapters or subchapters:
31 (1) Homicide, § 5-10-101 et seq.;
32 (2) Kidnapping and related offenses, § 5-11-101 et seq.;
33 (3) Sexual offenses, § 5-14-101 et seq.;
34 (4) Voyeurism offenses, § 5-16-101 et seq.;
35 (5) The Human Trafficking Act of 2013, § 5-18-101 et seq.;
36 (6) The Arkansas Protection of Children Against Exploitation Act
*CEB225*
04-14-2025 12:08:31 CEB225
As Engrossed: S4/8/25 S4/14/25 HB1865
1 of 1979, § 5-27-301 et seq.;
2 (7) Use of children in sexual performances, § 5-27-401 et seq.;
3 and
4 (8) Computer crimes against minors, § 5-27-601 et seq.
5 (c) The minimum term of imprisonment under an enhanced penalty under
6 this section is:
7 (1) Thirty (30) years for a Class Y felony;
8 (2) Fifteen (15) years for a Class A felony;
9 (3) Ten (10) years for a Class B felony;
10 (4) Five (5) years for a Class C felony; and
11 (5) One (1) year for a Class D felony.
12 (d) If an enhanced penalty is sought under this section, the
13 information or indictment shall include:
14 (1) That the enhanced penalty under this section is being
15 sought; and
16 (2) The allegations supporting the imposition of the enhanced
17 penalty under this section.
18
19 /s/Vaught
